Operations Advisor
01 May 2014 04:44 PM - UAE
..Duties Performed: 1. Plans, advises and coordinates the activities of assigned personnel in the Operations Division. 2. Participates in planning, coordination and recommendation of long and short term production programmes in conjunction with the Marketing Division. 3. Develops and advises on Operations Division Policies, strategies & objectives. 4. Advises on LNG & OAG plant and equipment performance to improve availability, reliability and safety. 5. Advises on the preparation of the annual budget for the Division, monitors expenditure and justifies the variances. 6. Advises on specialized contractors activities to ensure quality of workmanship and compliance with HSE & Engineering Standards. 7. Reviews existing Operating Procedures/Processes and develops additional ones as required. 8. Participates in the planning and coordination of overhaul programmes in conjunction with the Maintenance / Engineering and Integrity & Quality Divisions. 9. Optimizes plant operation, initiates plant and equipment modifications and reviews changes proposed by Departments Heads / Team Leaders to improve Plant efficiency & HSE. 10. Oversees impact of operations on environment by monitoring units, effluents, flaring, emissions and coordinates efforts for Plant-wide and International Standards. 11. Undertakes role of Operations Division Manager when required and directs activities accordingly. 12. Assists in Competency Assessment of Operations Staff & develops/reviews competency packages. Minimum Requirements: â¢ B.Sc. in Chemical Engineering or equivalent Engineering degree. â¢ 20 years' experience in Operations and Engineering activities in a petrochemical or oil refining or gas/ process industry (preferably in LNG), 10 years of which in a Senior Management role. â¢ Working knowledge of IT Systems used in process industry. â¢ Very Good knowledge of written and spoken English. â¢ Good Leadership, Team-building & communication skills. Note: please note that only Romanian candida